Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 08:12:53 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: contest list progress + admin users pagination
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Contest list now shows the caller's own progress (spec: returning to the
contest home screen should show "2/2 complétées" per contest):
- GET /contests now includes myProgress on each contest (questionsCompleted,
  xpTotal, isCompleted) when the caller has started a session on it, null
  otherwise. Previously the list had no per-user data at all — only the
  in-session view knew about progress, and it was lost the moment you went
  back to the list.

Pagination for the admin student list (backlog 9.1.2):
- GET /admin/users now accepts page/pageSize and returns
  { data, pagination: { page, pageSize, total, totalPages } } instead of a
  raw array. Previously there was no pagination anywhere — the whole
  student list was always fetched at once, on both API and UI.
- Breaking response-shape change — paired frontend patch updates the admin
  app's caller accordingly.

165/165 tests passing (20/20 suites), verified against a local Prisma
client stub as usual in this sandbox.
